x4freetext: Category I samples, (Na-24 as their standard),
The samples for activation resonance integral was
selected having no prominent resonances for the
The cadmium covered sample was irradiated
simultaneously with sodium which was used as the
Since there are no prominent resonances, there is no
Category II samples, (Au-197 as their standard)
Measurements of resonance integrals were made by
irradiating the samples bare and cadmium covered in
the pneumatic tube. Then the integrals were calculated
and diluted and irradiated in liquid form in order to
avoid the self-shielding effect of the resonance
